   bio:"Antoine Gilbert joined Leonides four years ago following a solid, if unspectacular, Formula 2 career. His time in Formula One has been a persistent challenge, with a career-best finish of P7 in 2023 and frequent difficulty advancing beyond Q1 in qualifying.\n\nTeam Principal Markus Schuster has repeatedly defended Gilbert's ability, attributing the team's on-track struggles to car performance and development limitations rather than any shortfall in driver skill — a view echoed by many in the paddock who rate Gilbert's raw talent highly.\n\n2025 brings a change of scenery for the Frenchman, racing alongside a rookie teammate for the first time rather than Ian Mallory, who consistently had the upper hand over him throughout 2024. It's a new dynamic that Gilbert will hope brings a change in fortunes.",
