   achievements:null, wins:0, podiums:0, poles:0,
   bio:"Julian \"Mick\" Carmichael has built his Formula One career on loyalty and steady improvement. After two seasons with Xtreme Motorsport — the outfit later succeeded by ACXS — Carmichael chose stability over reinvention, joining MerQury in 2019 rather than following the new American project. It's a decision that has paid dividends: since then, he has climbed the standings gradually but surely, culminating in a career-best P5 finish in the 2024 championship as MerQury itself rose to P4 in the Constructors' standings, its best result since the early 2010s.\n\nCarmichael's growth with the team reflects a broader upward trajectory for MerQury, and the Australian has become a central figure in that progress, valued as much for his race-day intelligence as his raw pace.\n\nOff the track, Carmichael's reputation extends well beyond results. Widely regarded as one of the most spirited and good-humoured personalities on the grid, he's known for lifting the mood in the paddock with a joke and an encouraging word. Teammates past and present, including Matthew Cox and Gerrit Van Dijk, consistently speak of him as one of the most well-liked drivers in the sport.",
