   achievements:"2 x WDC", wins:0, podiums:0, poles:0,
   bio:"Few drivers have climbed the ranks with the single-minded focus of Leon Radvan. Coming through Polish and wider European karting circuits, Radvan built his name on relentless determination long before he ever sat in a Formula One car. That drive carried him to a Formula One debut in 2018, at just 18 years old — the youngest driver in the sport's history — with Faucon, a team that had recognised his potential early and welcomed him into its academy as soon as he moved into single-seaters.\n\nRadvan spent two formative seasons with the French outfit before making the move to the considerably more competitive Refresh in 2020, a switch that would elevate him into genuine title contention. What followed was one of the sport's most compelling ongoing rivalries, as Radvan went head-to-head with Callum Sykes for the championship year after year. He came out on top in both 2022 and 2023, claiming back-to-back titles.\n\n2024 ended in heartbreak, with Radvan losing the championship to Sykes by a mere five points after a season-long battle. He enters 2025 with clear motivation to reclaim the title, and Refresh has built its 2025 car with his driving style firmly in mind — a partnership fully focused on getting Radvan back to the top of the standings.",
