   achievements:null, wins:0, podiums:0, poles:0,
   bio:"Magnus Osterrhein's path through Formula One has been defined by perseverance rather than early success. He made his debut with Refresh in 2015 but never quite lived up to the expectations placed on him, spending four seasons with the team before moving to Cavalla Nera's junior outfit, VenturoGrigio, in 2019. When VG was acquired by Luigi Altera in 2021 and rebranded as Frecciata, Osterrhein retained his seat through the transition.\n\nHis results have broadly matched what's expected of a low-midfield team, delivering steady if unspectacular performances over the years. But with Frecciata's competitiveness on the rise, the German now faces growing pressure to prove his value to a team with increasingly ambitious targets.\n\nA P11 finish in 2024 marked a step in the right direction, though Frecciata has made clear it expects its drivers inside the top ten going forward. Whether Osterrhein can meet that bar in 2025 will likely determine his long-term future with the team.",
