   achievements:null, wins:0, podiums:0, poles:0,
   bio:"Martin Courtois arrived in Formula One with significant expectations, earning a Refresh seat straight off the back of a third-place finish in the 2018 F2 Championship. Billed alongside Leon Radvan and Callum Sykes as one of the sport's next great talents, Courtois found the step up more difficult than anticipated, and his Refresh contract was cut short after just two seasons.\n\nA move to Equin followed in 2021, before Courtois found a more settled home at ACXS starting in 2023, where he has remained since. Team Principal Bernardo Miranda has been a vocal advocate for the Frenchman, arguing that Courtois never received a fair opportunity during his time at Refresh.\n\nWhile his P15 finish in 2024 doesn't yet reflect that belief, ACXS remains committed to proving that Courtois can compete nearer the front of the grid when given the right environment and time to develop.",
