   achievements:null, wins:0, podiums:0, poles:0,
   bio:"Matthew Cox's career has been marked by both promise and adversity. After four years with Faucon to start his Formula One journey, Cox joined MerQury in 2021 and appeared to be on a steady upward trajectory. That progress was interrupted in 2023, when a family bereavement kept him away from the grid for the entire season.\n\nEven while absent from racing, Cox remained on MerQury's books as a reserve driver, and the team's faith was rewarded when he returned partway through 2024, replacing José Torres with 13 races remaining. His comeback was nothing short of remarkable — three podium finishes, including two second-place results, in a compressed run of races that reminded the paddock exactly what he was capable of.\n\nHaving closed that chapter with MerQury at the end of 2024, Cox now takes on a fresh challenge with Frecciata for 2025 — a bold move into a team on the rise, and one he'll be hoping continues the momentum of his remarkable return.",
