   bio:"Oskar Hajek arrives in Formula One as one of the most eagerly anticipated rookies in years. Raised in Brno, Hajek began karting at age seven and quickly built a reputation across European junior circuits for his fearless overtaking and calm decision-making under pressure — traits that caught the attention of scouts well before his teenage years were over.\n\nAs a graduate of the Kinghorn Junior Academy Programme, Hajek's rise through the ranks has been closely guided by the team, culminating in a dominant F2 title in 2024. That championship-winning form has earned him a seat at the very top level, stepping into the car vacated by three-time champion Kieran William — a daunting task for any young driver.\n\nBoth Kinghorn Team Principal George Tills and veteran teammate Alexander Everill have publicly backed Hajek to adapt quickly and compete with the sport's best. With one of the most experienced drivers on the grid alongside him, Hajek has an ideal mentor as he begins to find his feet at the sport's highest level.",
